1. cs.AI - The paper proposes a Machine Learning (ML) based framework for the non-intrusive Parametric Model Order Reduction (PMOR) strategy. 
2. cs.LG - The ML model used in the proposed framework is designed to take into consideration the temporal evolution of the state solutions, which is a common problem in machine learning. 
3. cs.NA - The paper deals with the problem of reducing the computational cost of simulating changing well locations in an oil field, which involves numerical analysis techniques. 
4. cs.CE - The paper proposes a methodology for well placement optimization, which is a common problem in computational engineering. 
5. cs.SE - The paper proposes a workflow that is formulated such that all the simulation time steps are independent, which is a common problem in software engineering.
